WEBVTT

00:00.314 --> 00:03.064
<i>In the fall of 2011,</i>
<i>Lily and Marshall received</i>

00:03.065 --> 00:05.098
<i>a surprising gift</i>
<i>from Lily's grandparents:</i>

00:05.100 --> 00:06.850
<i>their house in Long Island.</i>

00:06.852 --> 00:10.820
<i>Lily and Marshall decided to</i>
<i>sell it for one simple reason.</i>

00:10.822 --> 00:12.188
It's Long Island.

00:12.190 --> 00:14.574
I don't want to spend
my Saturday in Long Island.

00:14.576 --> 00:15.859
I know, babe,

00:15.861 --> 00:17.944
but the realtor staged the
place with fake furniture

00:17.946 --> 00:20.330
and she wants us to check it
out before the open house.

00:20.332 --> 00:21.348
All right.

00:21.350 --> 00:23.366
Can we at least do it
on the fake bed?

00:23.368 --> 00:26.336
I'm embarrassed
that you have to ask.

00:26.338 --> 00:28.371
<i>So, they headed out</i>
<i>to Long Island,</i>

00:28.373 --> 00:31.274
<i>and when they walked</i>
<i>in the door...</i>

00:31.276 --> 00:33.076
We'll take it!

00:33.078 --> 00:34.427
We-We can't take it.

00:34.429 --> 00:36.262
We're the ones selling it.

00:36.264 --> 00:38.431
We are selling it, right?

00:38.433 --> 00:40.517
Baby, your grandparents gave
you this house outright.

00:40.519 --> 00:42.585
So, the way I see it,
we have five options.

00:42.587 --> 00:43.686
One: sell it.

00:43.688 --> 00:45.889
Two: year-round
haunted house.

00:45.891 --> 00:49.926
Three: giant fence around the
perimeter, chimp sanctuary.

00:49.928 --> 00:51.260
There's already a tire
swing in the backyard.

00:51.262 --> 00:53.563
Four: we destroy it
with sledgehammers.

00:53.565 --> 00:55.281
I like four.

00:55.283 --> 00:58.701
Or five: we move in,
raise our children

00:58.703 --> 01:00.770
and make this our family home.

01:00.772 --> 01:03.123
Till they graduate.

01:03.125 --> 01:05.992
Then we destroy it
with sledgehammers.

01:05.994 --> 01:08.795
As a family.

01:08.797 --> 01:10.747
No, this is crazy!

01:10.749 --> 01:11.998
We are New York people.

01:12.000 --> 01:14.617
We have a big, beautiful
apartment that we love.

01:14.619 --> 01:15.718
You're right.

01:15.720 --> 01:17.120
<i>But something happened</i>

01:17.122 --> 01:18.505
to Lily and Marshall that day.

01:18.507 --> 01:20.306
<i>Something that happens</i>
<i>to all New Yorkers</i>

01:20.308 --> 01:23.143
<i>who return home from anywhere</i>
<i>other than New York.</i>

01:23.145 --> 01:25.979
Their big, lovely apartment...

01:25.981 --> 01:27.847
Huh. That's weird.

01:29.466 --> 01:31.684
<i>...shrank.</i>

